<subSubSection box="[151,379,1210,1237]" pageId="10" pageNumber="197" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,379,1210,1237]" box="[151,379,1210,1237]" pageId="10" pageNumber="197">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,379,1210,1237]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="10" pageNumber="197" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,379,1210,1237]" pageId="10" pageNumber="197">
The 
<taxonomicName box="[207,296,1210,1236]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caspica">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[207,296,1210,1236]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="197">caspica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="197" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1281,1450]" pageId="10" pageNumber="197">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1281,1306]" pageId="10" pageNumber="197">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Members of this group can be recognized by (
<number box="[796,808,1282,1306]" pageId="10" pageNumber="197" value="1.0">1</number>
) the claw like outgrowth below embolus, (
<number box="[1290,1305,1282,1306]" pageId="10" pageNumber="197" value="2.0">2</number>
) the almost straight diagonal course of seminal duct, (
<number box="[633,647,1318,1342]" pageId="10" pageNumber="197" value="3.0">3</number>
) the short and wide embolus starting from 
<number box="[1146,1202,1318,1342]" pageId="10" pageNumber="197" value="9.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="9.0">9–10</number>
o’clock, and (
<number box="[1369,1384,1318,1342]" pageId="10" pageNumber="197" value="4.0">4</number>
) the wide semicircular epigynal fovea lacking septum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1281,1450]" pageId="10" pageNumber="197">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,351,1389,1414]" pageId="10" pageNumber="197">Composition</emphasis>
. We place two species in this group: 
<taxonomicName authority="Dunin, 1984" authorityName="Dunin" authorityYear="1984" box="[784,1117,1389,1414]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apscheronica">
<emphasis box="[784,967,1389,1414]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="197">B. apscheronica</emphasis>
Dunin, 
<number box="[1061,1117,1390,1414]" pageId="10" pageNumber="197" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ponomarev, 1979" authorityName="Ponomarev" authorityYear="1979" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caspica">
<emphasis box="[1176,1295,1390,1413]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="197">B. caspica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ponomarev" pageId="10" pageNumber="197" refString="Ponomarev, A. V. (1979) New species of spiders of the family Gnaphosidae from the North Caspian territory. Zoologicheskiy Zhurnal, 58, 921 - 923. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1979">
Ponomarev, 
<number box="[151,210,1426,1450]" pageId="10" pageNumber="197" value="1979.0">1979</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. It is very likely that these two species are synonyms.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
